The paper discusses a learning algorithm for determinantal point processes, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. The paper focuses on the task of learning the DPP kernel, which is a key component of DPPs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the numerical performance of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
